📊 Sales & Customer Performance Dashboards (Tableau)

This project consists of two interactive Tableau dashboards — Sales Dashboard and Customer Dashboard — designed to help stakeholders such as sales managers, marketing teams, and executives analyze key performance metrics, monitor trends, and gain insights into overall business performance.

The dashboards provide year-over-year comparisons, trend analysis, and interactive filtering to enable data-driven decision-making.

🎯 Objectives

Monitor sales performance and profitability over time.
Understand customer behavior, loyalty, and segmentation.

Enable users to interactively explore data and uncover actionable insights.


📈 Dashboards Overview

🛍️ Sales Dashboard
Purpose:
Provide an overview of sales metrics and trends to analyze year-over-year performance and identify key sales drivers.

Key Features:

KPI Overview: Displays total sales, profits, and quantities for the current and previous years.

Sales Trends: Monthly trend charts for sales, profit, and quantity with clear identification of highest and lowest months.

Product Subcategory Comparison: Compare sales and profit performance across subcategories for both years.

Weekly Trends: Weekly sales and profit visualization with average line highlighting above/below-average performance.


👥 Customer Dashboard
Purpose:
Provide insights into customer data, trends, and behaviors to support marketing and retention strategies.

Key Features:
KPI Overview: Displays total customers, total sales per customer, and total number of orders for the current and previous years.

Customer Trends: Monthly analysis of customer KPIs with visual highlights for peak and low months.

Customer Distribution: Visualization of customers by number of orders to understand engagement and loyalty levels.

Top 10 Customers by Profit: Highlights the most profitable customers, including their rank, order count, total sales, profit, and last order date.

🧭 Design & Interactivity
Dynamic Dashboard: Users can select any desired year to analyze historical data.
Seamless Navigation: Easy switch between Sales and Customer dashboards.
Interactive Visuals: Charts are clickable and can act as filters.
Advanced Filtering:
Product-based filters: Category, Subcategory
Location-based filters: Region, State, City

🗂️ Data
The dashboards are built using sales and customer datasets that include key fields such as:
Sales Data: Order Date, Sales, Profit, Quantity, Category, Subcategory, Region, State, City.
Customer Data: Customer ID, Customer Name, Number of Orders, Total Sales, Profit, Last Order Date.

🧠 Tools & Technologies
Tableau Desktop / Tableau Public
Excel or CSV datasets (for input)

🚀 How to Use
Open the Tableau file (.twbx) in Tableau Desktop or Tableau Public.
go MOde Preview or presentation and explore both dashboards through the navigation buttons.
Use filters to analyze specific years, regions, or product categories.
Interact with charts to drill down into specific data points.



